# Favicon: Red Georgia T Only

The site favicon is a **burgundy Georgia serif "T"** (`#941E2F`), never the cream/orange corner-triangle UI motif.

## Never change without explicit user request

Do **not** edit, regenerate, reorder, or replace any file in `public/favicon*`, `public/apple-touch-icon.png`, or `views/partials/seo-head.ejs` favicon links unless the user explicitly asks.

## Forbidden icon

The corner-triangle favicon (cream `#EFE8DC` + orange `#C16A28` wedge) must never appear in favicon assets. It is a **navigation UI element**, not the tab icon.

## Required assets (all must show the red T)

- `public/favicon.svg` — Georgia `T` text, `#941E2F`
- `public/favicon-16.png`, `favicon-32.png`, `favicon-48.png`
- `public/apple-touch-icon.png`
- `/favicon.ico` is served by Express as a copy of `favicon-32.png` (no separate .ico file)

## If favicons must be regenerated

Run:

```bash
npm run generate:favicon
```

Then confirm:

```bash
npm run verify:favicon
```

## New pages

All pages must include favicons only through `views/partials/seo-head.ejs` (which includes `favicon-links.ejs`). Do not add separate favicon links unless updating those partials for the whole site.

**Do not link `favicon.svg` in HTML.** Browsers render SVG favicons at a different size than the locked PNG tab icons. Tab icons must use the PNG/ICO assets only.
